rComments: Tries her best to make the labs run smoothly. However, the lab itself is difficult and I almost never knew what was actually going on until after I had written the report. The practical midterms are EXTREMELY easy and the final is doable, although it is definitely the hardest aspect of the course. Do well on reports and midterms and you'll succeed.
Very good teacher. She cares a lot about her students. Difficult course but she is the best you can have the course with

Prof McGilvray is really friendly and helpful during office hours. I found this course to be really fun. Only issue is lab material is ahead of lecture for a few weeks which makes lab reports harder to write. You need to UNDERSTAND WHY you did things in the lab and why you are doing lab in first place. Practical exams were very easy if you studied.

Bottom line: prepare before the labs & they'll be easy. Reports: depends on TA, do ur mechanisms correctly, a little time consuming. Practicals: easy if you paid attention during the labs. Final: super hard, we didn't have material to study from, just our labs. Make sure to do well in lab reports cuz your grade will take a hit after the final.

She is nice & approachable. The course is very doable. To do well read the lab manual carefully cuz it explains concepts that u need to understand for the labs. Labs are easy if you come prepared. Preparation for the lab doesn't take more than 1 hour beforehand. Practicals: super easy, over basic techniques. Final: brutal, dropped my grade 6%. GL!

The prof herself is a nice and caring lady . Practical exam questions were fair. Final was fair,but tough because you dont have a note to study, just your lab knowledge. Past exams will help. You have a lab report due every week (a disaster). The reports are intense. Don't do this course with other tough or intense courses, it is TIME CONSUMING.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Somewhere between first and second year the standards for lab reports went way up and no one informed us. The labs are complicated and demand a real understanding of concepts in chemistry. Lab rapports are always long. Get ready for lab reports in teams of 4 that are due in 24h. Hope you get a good and easy grading TA.
Literally her answers for at least half of the questions she gives us are wrong. Even on her marking scheme for an exam. How are we supposed to learn if the prof can't even do her own questions?

The orgo 2 lab will raise your GPA if you're good at writing lab reports, there were 7 experiments, 2 practical exams and 1 final. Watch out for the practical exams, they're pretty hard unless you study religiously for them.

She's really caring and tries her best, but often mixes up her words and people end up confused. She spent lots of time explaining things again because she was unclear. Not terrible at teaching, but there is certainly better. Still, course wasn't too hard and if you try can do well.

This prof is a really great person and she definitely cares about her students but she makes the course so much harder than it needs to be. The midterms are ridiculously long (almost the same length as the final which is absurd...) and you really need to study a lot if you want to do more than just pass. AVOID this prof is you want a good grade
The overall course was fine, but the final is much harder than what the rest of the course was. Study a lot.

Your experience in this class really depends on your TA, the prof herself is very down to earth and wants her students to understand. The pre-labs are easy, the midterm is difficult and the lab reports are okay but make sure you have the right mechanisms as they are graded very strictly and are done differently than the ones seen in 2520.

How easy this class is really depends on your TA. The lab manual is well-written, and the labs themselves are fairly well run. Prelabs and postlabs are easy. Lab reports don't take too long, but if your TA is really strict you're gonna need to put in some extra work here. Final was straightforward, practical midterm was very easy if you studied.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Amazing! So caring and so accommodating. She really has the students best interest at heart. The labs are difficult at times but she makes sure things run smoothly the best she can.
If you enjoyed organic chem 1 with Dr. beauchemain you will definitely love Dr. Katherine McGilvray . She uses the same reversed  class method that worked very well with me.
Best teacher in the science department. Everything is clear and well explained and the correction is fair. What would you ask more! but prepare yourself to do small homeworks every week.

She gives you litterally everything you need to succeed. Plus, she makes herself available for her students not only after class and at office hours but you can also make appointments with her. Definitely one of the best teachers I've had in university, and trust me, I didn't get many.

Prof McGilvray really cares and wants you to do well. She posted past midterms and exams for us to study, but of course she changes stuff so don't rely on just that. Do her problem sets and homework. Go to all the classes. Make sure your notes are complete. Memorize all the mechanisms and understand all the lab concepts. You have to work to succeed

Lectures were recorded so showing up wasn't mandatory. Echo 360 was used which made it easy to ask questions online. Prof McGilvray cares about students and tries to answer all questions, however her lectures are slow as she stops a lot when people have questions. We had to 'teach ourselves' whatever she didn't cover in class.

Katherine is one of the nicest profs I've ever had, loved her! Everyone that has her for the orgo lab seems to hate, I don't know why cause I had her for orgo 1 and she's straight up with you when you ask her a question. Midterms as well as the final were more than fair. It's not her fault there's 20 mechanisms you need to memorize.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Katherine was an amazing lab coordinator. She had to deal with over 700 students and during every office hour she stayed until everyone was gone. Her midterm is a bit tough but if you do better on the final she gets rid of the midterm mark which is almost exactly the same except longer. Easy A in my opinion and she's very understanding. :)
I need to say good bye to medical school now :( AVOID HER

Very unorganized, especially for someone who's been teaching so long. Extremely specific marking scheme that you really can't predict. Midterm was terrible but final reflected course content a lot more closely, and the midterm was dropped if your final was better. Make sure to go in and check your final, lots of people had missing marks.

RUN FOREST RUN!!  I can not stress how stupid this class is. I feel like lab reports should be worth more since they directly reflect the labs. As for the midterm that was a bomb, half the class failed, and the exam was just as stupid, her marking scheme is horrendous so everyone does worse than they expected. I would not recommend taking this lab
Her exams are definitely difficult, and have a strict marking scheme. Very nice professor though.

McGilvray is a stunning, kind and smart lady. She does care about her students. People think an orgo 2 lab course is easy? Seriously, no. It requires work. You need to actually be good in organic chemistry to succeed this class. Most of the final stuff was covered in her review and the midterm was fair. I got an A  on it...! Easy A+ in my opinion

Worst professor. She would show up to the lab, stay for maybe an hour and a half, and then leave. If you ask her a question, she would shrug you off and say that she doesn't know the answer. Midterm was impossible, although the final was okay. The marking scheme is so unclear, and if you don't write EXACTLY what she wants, you're wrong.

labs are based on a rubric you dont even get to see????? midterm marking scheme proved that you to read her mind to know exactly what she wanted. never seen anyone turn straightforward material into something half the class ends up failing. i think theres something wrong with how the test was graded if half the class fails

While the lab manual was fairly clear and the labs somewhat relevant to orgo II, that midterm was hell on earth. Literally half of like 700 kids got a 50 or below. The marking scheme was so specific and made you want to punch something in the face. Seems like a nice person and initially answered questions on blackboard, but suddenly stopped.

Dr. Mcgilvray was an absolute angel! I dont understand the hate! Hands down one of the best chem professors. Thanks to her class I got accepted into the McGill medical college right out of 3rd year. Uni and colleges can def use more professors like her. Crystal clear and exam highly reflects what was covered in the course. No surprises whatsoever!

She doesn't understand her own marking scheme, purposely inflates course content to make the average to a lower standard than CHM2120, the midterm was horrific, final exam was a joke but the marking once again was inflation to reduce the courses average. Prompted TA's to give lower marks on TA evaluation and labs for these reasons also. Low ethics

The course material SHOULD be quite easy but 1) prof has *important* clarity issues. Manual full of typos, meaningless sentences, etc. French translation even worse. When you tell her, she a) thinks it's funny. b) obviously doesn't realize all the problems she causes. 2) doesn't communicate *important* info by fear of cheaters who would sell it.

Katherine doesn't really understand the labs herself so that can be problematic. She can't answer questions in a helpful way. The midterm was very long, the final was a reasonable length. Pray you have a good TA because the TA makes or breaks the course. Be prepared to be tested on CHM 2120 material that was never mentioned in the lab.

As a lab coordinator, she has a big job and she does it fairly well. The labs are pretty long on average, like 3 hours are rushed. The lab manual is pretty useful. The midterm was pretty hard, the final was okay. Understand the lab before doing it and it's not bad. Apart from that, she is nice and pretty helpful for questions.

I don't know where these easiness levels of 3 and 4 are coming from. She makes the exames out of more so you do worse. She knows nothing about organic chemistry, is less than useless at helping students. Incompetent does not even begin to describe this woman. WORST PROF EVER! She's the Anti-Prof. The lab manual is all wrong. Just an awful prof

Labs are marked easy, the pre-lab quizzes are marked rigidly and the marking scheme for the exam was altered after it was written to lower the class avg. As the coordinater shes pretty useless. It was almost impossible to see the exam after it was marked (this is ridiculous imo) but still a pretty easy class to do well in if you study.

The exam was pretty tough. Everyoen thought it was easy, but the average was low. The quizzes were also hard. You had to get exactly what they wanted or you did not get the points. also, you need to get a good TA which really comes down to luck. In general, she wants to help you, but doesn't know much
It really all comes down to your TA.  Write your report the way your TA likes it, and you'll be rolling in good grades.  Also, very easy final exam - satisfying and fair :)
Quizzes were tough but her exam was much more leniant.  Overall good course.

She tries her best to help you when you ask her a question and is extremely helpful and nice in general. The quizzes are a bit tough but that's because the TA's are extremely picking on the marking. The final exam marking was much more lenient.

Dr. McGilvray was an excellent lab coordinator. As previously stated her french isn't flawless but she does her best to accommodate everyone. Final exam was very straight forward and much easier than the final given in previous years. Doing well on lab reports and quizzes are key so take them seriously as they can be difficult otherwise.

Took the class in French, she claims she is bilingual, but she cannot even maintain a conversation in French. Her quizzes and final exam were very tough and took a long time to do. She can't write an exam, especially not in French. Her questions rarely reflect the answer desired/expected. Experiments are fun to do, but sometimes tough.

She's a really nice and friendly person; she's always around helping out in the lab. She even responds daily on the discussion board! Only downside is that she's a bit tough, her prelab quizzes and questions in the lab manual are challenging. She is the best lab coordinator I've had and her lab manual is clearly written!
